This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification using deep learning techniques. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of pre-trained models and fine-tuning for a specific task suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) as it involves classification of skin lesions based on visual features. Finally, the use of multi-scale CNNs suggests that it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with processing of visual data.
